title: 'Wolverine' Podcast Returning for Season 2
excerpt: 'Wolverine: The Lost Trail' will bring Richard Armitage back as the feral mutant hero, starting in winter 2019.
description: The second season will follow Wolverine to New Orleans after the dramatic climax of Wolverine: The Long Night, where he discovers that a number of mutants and humans have gone missing in the city. Setting out to investigate, he’ll run into two names familiar to longtime X-Men comic book fans: Jason Wyngarde and Remy LeBeau, better known as the villainous Mastermind and the cajun thief Gambit, respectively.

summary: Catch it? Hell no. I’ll just...talk to it. Most ghosts are lost people or pets searching for their owners. Once they accept what...
body:
Catch it? Hell no. I’ll just…talk to it. Most ghosts are lost people or pets searching for their owners. Once they accept what happened, they move on.

99% of the ghosts I find can’t harm anyone, most of them don’t even mean to, there’s no reason to take them out. When I find an evil one I just…give them a little push so they’ll move on faster.

body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2Pf15q3

by Marstars232

Once May dies,Tony takes in Peter for only being fifteen,is like a son to him and gets along great with the Avengers. But Pepper not taking Tony back means he couldn’t take the real experience of being a natural father at all.Thankfully with the agreement of the team though,to not only treat Peter like the baby Avenger for his age.All they have to do is make him play his role better,and he won’t be hurt anymore by anyone as long as the team is there to protect him.

Peter though doesn’t get a say or choice on their minds.Plus May isn’t with him to change their minds or allow him back into the apartment.
